techmeme.title: Sundar Pichai says "more than a quarter of all new code at Google is generated by AI, then reviewed and accepted by engineers" (Jay Peters/The Verge)

Sources: Chinese hackers targeted phones used by Trump family members and Biden admin and State Dept. officials; audio communications may have been captured (New York Times)
Snap says it will roll out its new "simple" Snapchat app in Q1 2025, ~10M users are testing it, but warns the engagement metrics are worse on iOS versus Android (Alex Weprin/The Hollywood Reporter)
AMD reports Q3 revenue up 18% YoY to $6.82B, vs. $6.71B est., Data Center revenue up 122% to $3.5B, and Q4 revenue forecast below est.; AMD drops 5% after hours (Arsheeya Bajwa/Reuters)
